==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''Δημήτηρ''' (''Demeter''), from '''[[Δή]]''' (''De''), an early form of '''[[Γή]]''' (''Ge'') "earth" + '''[[μήτηρ]]''' (''meter'') "mother". [[Category:Greek derivations]]

===Proper Noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
{{wikipedia}}
#{{greekmyth}} The goddess of <big><big><big><big><big><big><big>PENISthe fertility of the [[Earth]] and [[harvest]]s, protector of marriage and social order; daughter of [[Cronos]] and [[Rhea]], mother to [[Persephone]]

